The paper is about designing a semantic segmentation network using neural architecture search (NAS) to achieve state-of-the-art performance and faster speed. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of NAS also suggests the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed decoupled and fine-grained latency regularization and teacher-student distillation techniques involve optimization and training methods, which could place the paper in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, making the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category a possibility as well.
